BT 1 0 0 1 0 99 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Bone is piezoelectric \(Fukada & Yasuda 1957\). Mechanical stress applied to bone crystal structure generates an electrical) Tj T* (potential. This potential guides osteoblast \(bone-building\) and osteoclast \(bone-resorbing\) activity via Wolff's Law \(1892\):) Tj T* (bone remodels along lines of mechanical stress. The mapping to the Wike framework is exact: mechanical stress =) Tj T* (gamma_eff perturbation; the piezoelectric signal = the body's measurement of that perturbation; osteoblast/osteoclast) Tj T* (response = the biological Le Chatelier restoring force \(Paper 69\). Below gamma_c: the system remodels to absorb the) Tj T* (stress \(Le Chatelier\). Above gamma_c: stress fracture \(topological defect, Paper 53\) and osteoporosis \(C_0 loss, Paper) Tj T* (63\). The Earth itself is piezoelectric at geological scale: quartz, calcite, and apatite \(the mineral of bone\) are all piezoelectric) Tj T* (crystals. Geological tipping points \(earthquakes, Paper 83\) occur when accumulated stress drives the rock's gamma_eff to) Tj T* (gamma_c -- at which point topological defects \(faults\) form.) Tj T* ET
